I am building a validation-first, non-diagnostic Feline Grimace Scale research prototype for the Kaggle Gemma 4 Good Hackathon. The project is explicitly framed as triage support / education only, not veterinary diagnosis.

I found your Scientific Reports article, “Chatbot assessment of acute pain in cats using the Feline Grimace Scale: comparative study” (DOI: 10.1038/s41598-025-27404-z), and its Supplementary Material 1 spreadsheet with 50 image IDs and expert gold-standard FGS ratios.

Would you be willing to share the corresponding 50 cat images, or provide guidance on whether/how they can be accessed for non-commercial research validation? The public spreadsheet is very useful, but without the matching images I cannot run an image-based validation.

